The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, January 06, 2004 				 HPL debt recast awaits lenders nod
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Calcutta, Jan. 5: The corporate debt-restructuring cell of IDBI will announce Haldia Petrochemicals loan rejig within 10-12 days. This is the time that lenders will take to get permission from their boards for the package. The two main promoters of Rs 5,170-crore HPL  The Chatterjee Group and the Bengal government  met officials of IDBI in Mumbai today.																								Bengal commerce and industry secretary Sabyasachi Sen, who represented the state government at the meeting, said: We had the last meeting of the promoters. Negotiations are over. IDBI will announce the package within 10-12 days. Chatterjee Group boss Purnendu Chatterjee was also present.																								Sen said the debt-revamp package for HPL was ready, but refused to spell out the contents. We will not be able to talk about it until all lenders approve it, he added. 
